- e2e/browser-inspection.e2e.ts (NEW)

Context:
Follow the exact pattern from `e2e/browser-tools.e2e.ts`. Use fixtures: `mcpServer`, `extensionContext`, `mcpClient`, `testServer`. The standard setup:

```typescript
import type { McpClient, McpServer, TestServer } from './fixtures.js';
import { expect, test } from './fixtures.js';
import { BROWSER_TOOL_NAMES, parseToolResult, waitForExtensionConnected, waitForLog } from './helpers.js';

const initAndListTools = async (mcpServer: McpServer, mcpClient: McpClient) => {
  await waitForExtensionConnected(mcpServer);
  await waitForLog(mcpServer, 'plugin(s) mapped');
  return mcpClient.listTools();
};
```

For each tool, create a `test.describe` block with:
1. 'appears in tools/list' — verify name is in the list
2. 'returns data for a test page' — open test server tab, call tool, verify response structure
3. 'returns error for invalid tabId' — call with tabId: 999999, expect isError: true

For accessibility tree, open the test server page (which has HTML elements), then:
```typescript
const result = await mcpClient.callTool('browser_get_accessibility_tree', { tabId });
expect(result.isError).toBe(false);
const data = parseToolResult(result.content);
expect(data.nodes).toBeDefined();
expect(Array.isArray(data.nodes)).toBe(true);
expect(data.nodes.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
```

For performance metrics:
```typescript
const data = parseToolResult(result.content);
expect(data.dom).toBeDefined();
expect(typeof data.dom.nodes).toBe('number');
expect(data.memory || data.heap).toBeDefined();
```

For security info — the test server is HTTP (not HTTPS), so expect securityState to be 'insecure' or 'neutral'.

For memory — verify dom.nodes and heap.usedBytes are numbers > 0.

For audit page — the test page may have zero issues, so just verify the response structure has the expected category fields.

Constraints:
- Use openTestServerTab helper to open a tab (see browser-tools.e2e.ts pattern)
- Each tool test needs its own tab since the debugger can only attach once per tab
- Use waitFor if CDP commands need time to stabilize
